    {"instruction": "Is it better to proxy or play budget substitutions?", "input": "", "output": "It depends on the event. Many local game stores allow proxies for Legacy events, which lets you play the optimal list. MTGO does not use proxies but cards are much cheaper ($300-650 for most decks). For competitive events (SCG Opens, Grand Prix), proxies are not allowed and you need real cards or budget substitutions. If your LGS allows proxies, absolutely use them to learn the deck at full power, then acquire real cards over time for larger events."},
